  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Food Sovereignty and Income Generation on the Northern Coast of Rio Grande do Sul and Southern Coast of Santa Catarina</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will be implemented in the Mampituba river valley and includes the states of Rio Grande do Sul and Santa Catarina. In this region, modernization of agriculture has impoverished farming families and degraded the landscape. To reverse this, ecological agriculture accompanied by new strategies for processing and marketing must be adopted by a growing number of families, and new forms of work and income generation must be created in urban areas. This project will work with farming families, training and enabling them to make the transition to agroecology. The project will also work to insert socially vulnerable families into the dynamics of production, on the basis of the principles of solidarity economics. Nearly 200 farming families will receive training in production, processing and marketing to diversify diet and market supply. Work with domestic food gardens and training for 30 families in the urban community will also improve diet while increasing job opportunities. Another 250 families will benefit from passing on the gift, through training methodologies in which the trainees from one stage are trainers for the subsequent stages.</narrative>
  </description>
